sed in the interstellar medium, the diffusion\ncoefficient is $2-30 \\cdot 10^{26}$ cm$^2$/s at 1 TeV, i.e. two orders of\nmagnitude smaller than the value considered to be the average in the Galaxy.\nThese observations imply that Galactic PWNe have low-diffusion bubbles with a\nsize of at least 80 pc.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 8 Aug 2019 18:00:02 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Mon, 6 Dec 2021 10:43:16 GMT"}],"update_date":"2021-12-07"}
