\n$p$ is small (e.g. from p~8% to p~7%).\n  Magnetic field geometry reduces the polarisation fraction in the simulated\nclumps by only \\Delta p~1% on average. The larger drop seen towards the actual\nPGCC clumps suggests some loss of grain alignment in the dense medium, such as\npredicted by the radiative torque mechanism. The statistical study is not able\nto quantify dust opacity changes at the scale of the PGCC clumps.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Fri, 9 Aug 2019 11:45:50 GMT"}],"update_date":"2019-09-25"}
