 $H\\alpha$, UV excess, and mass accretion rates at\nthe same level as full disk systems. We estimate the inner hole sizes, ranging\nfrom 0.1 to $78AU$, for the sample of transition disk candidates. In only\n$18\\%$ of the transition disk candidates, the hole size could be explained by\nX-ray photoevaporation from stellar radiation.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Fri, 9 Aug 2019 15:02:29 GMT"}],"update_date":"2019-09-11"}
